headline: 3 High-Yielding Dividend Stocks That Haven't Been This Cheap in Years
summary: Buying a quality dividend stock near a multiyear low can be a great move, especially if you're willing to be patient and hang on for the long term.  PepsiCo (NASDAQ: PEP), UnitedHealth Group (NYSE: UNH), and United Parcel Service (NYSE: UPS) are all down more than 15% in the past 12 months and are trading near multiyear lows.  Beverage and snack company PepsiCo has experienced a 25% decline in value over the past 12 months.
